channel.title: Port/server problem. please help
channel.description:
Hello, I recently reset my computer to factory default and now I cannot run a server. Even no-ip wont work it says error connecting to server. Before I did the reset I could run any server but now it says "Cannot Assign Requested Adress: JVM_BIND". I have port forwarded and everything. I tried to run another server and it said "Could not open the port 43594, it must be open in something else" but I have no clue what it would be open in. I tried to find it on some port check websites but it said nothings open.
Any help is appreciated. :)

item.description:

`Java:

[quote]“Could not open the port 43594, it must be open in something else”

Means you tried running your server while another server was already running.

Are you sure you reinstalled JDK?[/quote]

Absolutely positive. I updated it today. JDK JRE. The regular java. I am not running anyother server. As I said I could run one before the reset and I know for a fact I am not running one. Is it possible for someone to post the most common programs that use port 43594? And thank you java for your reply.

item.description:

Remember in portforwarding you can port forward something but most people forget you have to allow the application you portforwarded through your routers “Firewall” go back into your router and make sure you allowed it through the firewall. Should work then.
